SIMPLE: foreshorten
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Foreshorten
<hw>Fore*short"en</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Fine Art)</fld> <def>To represent on a plane surface, as if
extended in a direction toward the spectator or nearly so; to shorten by
drawing in perspective.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Fig.: To represent pictorially to the
imagination.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Songs, and deeds, and lives that lie⟦br⟧
<qex>Foreshortened</qex> in the tract of time.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Foreshortening</ent>⟦br⟧
